  "local_port": 42266,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you drop off a U-Haul at a different location?",
  "response": "To drop off a U-Haul at a different location, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Contact U-Haul**: Before you start your trip, call U-Haul at 1-800-GO-UHAUL (1-800-468-4285) to inform them of your intention to drop off the truck at a different location. They will need to confirm that the new location is an authorized U-Haul drop-off point.\n\n2. **Confirm Availability**: Ensure that the new drop-off location has space available for your truck. U-Haul will help you find a suitable location if the one you choose is full.\n\n3. **Adjust Your Reservation**: U-Haul will modify your rental agreement to reflect the new drop-off location. This may affect your rental charges, so ask about any potential changes in cost.\n\n4. **Document the Mileage**: When you pick up the truck, note the starting mileage. You'll need this information when you drop off the truck.\n\n5. **Drive to the New Location**: Safely drive the U-Haul truck to the new drop-off location.\n\n6. **Inspect the Truck**: Before returning the truck, inspect it for any damage that may have occurred during your rental period. Take photos if necessary.\n\n7. **Drop Off the Truck**: Once you arrive at the new location, find a U-Haul representative. Provide them with your rental agreement and the final mileage.\n\n8. **Complete the Drop-Off Process**: The U-Haul representative will inspect the truck and finalize the return process. They will note any new damages and calculate your final charges based on the mileage and any additional fees.\n\n9. **Receive Your Receipt**: After the drop-off is complete, you'll receive a receipt that details your rental charges. Keep this for your records.\n\nBy following these steps, you can successfully drop off your U-Haul at a different location. Remember to communicate with U-Haul throughout the process to ensure a smooth experience.",
